PKGMAN(1)

# NAME

pkgman - unified interface for package management

# SYNOPSIS

*pkgman* [*-Vh*] [*--no-std-config*] [*--config*=_config-file_] \
       [*--config-*{*set*,*append*,*prepend*}=_string_] \
       [*--root*=_root-dir_] [*--*] _command_ [_args_]

# DESCRIPTION

The *pkgman* utility extends the core package tools *pkgmk*(8),
*pkgadd*(8), *pkgrm*(8), and *pkginfo*(1).
It provides a unified interface and advanced functionality for
building, installing, updating, and querying software packages.

## Generic options

The following options are recognized by all *pkgman* commands.
Individual commands may define additional options and arguments.

*--no-std-config*
	Ignore the default configuration file.

*--config*=_config-file_
	Use an alternate configuration file.

	Default: _/etc/pkgman.conf_.

*--config-set*=_string_
	Set a configuration entry, overriding the _config-file_ value.

*--config-append*=_string_
	Append value to a configuration entry.

*--config-prepend*=_string_
	Prepend value to a configuration entry.

*--root*=_root-dir_
	Use an alternate root directory.

	Default: */*.

*-V*, *--version*
	Print version and exit.

*-h*, *--help*
	Show the manual page for _command_, or this page if no command
	is specified.

*--*
	Stop option parsing.
	If a _command_ was specified, remaining arguments are passed
	verbatim; otherwise the next arguments are treated as the
	_command_ and its _args_.

## Commands

The first non-option argument specifies the command name.
Commands are grouped into the following categories.

_Informational_:

*pkgman-dumpconfig*(1)
	Print current configuration.

*pkgman-list*(1)
	List available packages.

*pkgman-list-dup*(1)
	List duplicate packages.

*pkgman-list-nodependents*(1)
	List packages without dependents.

*pkgman-list-locked*(1)
	List locked packages.

*pkgman-list-orphans*(1)
	List orphaned packages.

*pkgman-printf*(1)
	Print formatted list of available packages.

*pkgman-info*(1)
	Display package information.

*pkgman-readme*(1)
	Print a package's README file.

*pkgman-path*(1)
	Print the path to a package source.

*pkgman-isinst*(1)
	Check if packages are installed.

*pkgman-current*(1)
	Print installed package version.

*pkgman-diff*(1)
	Show differences between installed and available packages.

_Dependency_:

*pkgman-dep*(1)
	Print dependencies for a package.

*pkgman-rdep*(1)
	Print reverse dependencies for a package.

_Search_:

*pkgman-search*(1)
	Search package source directories for package names.

*pkgman-dsearch*(1)
	Search package source directories for package names
	and descriptions.

*pkgman-fsearch*(1)
	Search package source directories for files listed in
	package footprints.

_Management_:

*pkgman-install*(8)
	Install packages.

*pkgman-update*(8)
	Update installed packages.

*pkgman-remove*(8)
	Remove installed packages.

_System update_:

*pkgman-sysup*(8)
	Update all outdated packages.

*pkgman-lock*(8)
	Lock packages to prevent updates.

*pkgman-unlock*(8)
	Unlock packages for update.

_File operations_:

*pkgman-ls*(1)
	List contents of a package source directory.

*pkgman-cat*(1)
	Display a file from a package source directory.

*pkgman-edit*(8)
	Edit a file from a package source directory.

# EXIT STATUS

*0*
	Command executed successfully.
*>0*
	An error occurred.

# FILES

_/etc/pkgman.conf_
	Configuration file.

	See *pkgman.conf*(5).

_/var/lib/pkg/db_
	Database of installed packages.

	See *packages*(7).

_/var/lib/pkg/locked_
	Database of locked packages, used by *pkgman-lock*(8),
	*pkgman-unlock*(8), and *pkgman-list-locked*(1).

When *--root*=_root-dir_ is specified, databases are read from and
written to _root-dir/var/lib/pkg/db_ and
_root-dir/var/lib/pkg/locked_.

